article.headline: San Diego St. 68, Colorado St. 59
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Tim Shelton and Ryan Amoroso each scored 14 points as San Diego State defeated Colorado State 68-59 on Wednesday. Kyle Spain added 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Aztecs (20-8, 10-5 Mountain West Conference), who led by three at halftime before building their largest lead of the game at 60-48 with 7:20 left. San Diego State, which beat the Rams 78-59 last month, opened the game on a 16-5 run. Colorado State (9-21, 4-12) outscored the Aztecs 16-10 over the final six minutes of the half and trailed 36-33. Marcus Walker led the Rams with 24 points.
